==Latin==
===Etymology===
Uncertain, possibly from Greek ''ioulos'' 'wooly first beard hares', i.e. the young, or from Latin ''Jovilius'' 'devoted to [[Jove]]'

===Noun===
'''Julius'''

# July (''month''; originally [[Quintilis]] 'the fifth' (starting from March), renamed after Caius Julius [[Caesar]])

[[Category:la:Praenomen]]

===Derivations===
* [[Julianus]] (Latin), hence [[Julian]] (English; also an adjective as in Julian calendar; also German), Julien (French), 
* [[Julienne]] (female name and soup), Juliet
* [[Giulio]] (Italian)
* [[Gillian]], [[Gill]] (female forms), hence [[gill]] (which has other homonyms)
* the month [[July]] (''English''), Juli (Dutch, German), Juillet (French) 
* [[yulyuz]] (''Tashelhet'')

